  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Exclusion Criteria

        Co-existing Condition:

        Patients with the following conditions are excluded:

          -  Opportunistic infection (Pneumocystis carinii pneumonia (PCP), cryptococcal
             meningitis) or other conditions (brain abscess) which would make treatment results
             difficult to interpret due to concurrent infection, disease, or therapy.

        Patients with other opportunistic infections or brain diseases are excluded.

        Patients with AIDS and cerebral toxoplasmosis.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
